For the creation of the Api documentation, yuidoc is used.

To install yuidoc, first install Node.js:
Download and install Node.js (http://nodejs.org/#download)

After that install yuidoc via the Node.js command prompt
npm -g install yuidocjs.

Very Important: copy the adapted docparser in 
<workspace>/Voice2SocialApp/doc/docparser.js
to
%USERPROFILE%\AppData\Roaming\npm\node_modules\yuidocjs\lib
so that category tags are parsed.

Now you can open a Node.js command prompt and go to the <workspace>/Voice2SocialApp/doc directory and execute create_doc.bat (Windows)

The documentation should be created in the <workspace>/Voice2SocialApp/doc/out directory
--> open <workspace>/Voice2SocialApp/doc/out/index.html